<br>
AD is dedicated to having fun and getting items for our friends and family.<br>
<br>
Unlike most guilds where you must wear the guild tag, we have an affiliate program which is used for our members who for one reason or another cannot wear our tag.  An affiliate is still a full member of AD.  An affiliate does go through a more stringent approval process then a &quot;tagged&quot; member however.  We love our affiliates but we need folks wearing the tag too..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Currently for non members/affialiates, we will accept applications from persons with a main character of level 51 or higher.  At this point we have no plans to raise that level, though for some of the places we go there are higher minimum levels required to be able to attend.<br>
<br>
We take the view of the Foreign Legion...once you are accepted your past is gone.  This is an excellent place to restart if you had a bad experience in a guild or even if you bought an account.  What we care about is you participate, don't act the ass, and that you know how to play your character well.<br>
<br>
For people that enjoy playing more than one character at a time, we're cool with that too...so long as you can actually play them.  We plan our raid startup times to give multiboxers more time to get to the raid and we plan for slower movement though bad areas to accomodate this as well.<br>
<br>
Currently we farm Armor en masse from the Kael Arena.  Starting in November, 2002 we will shift our main guild activities to the Halls of Testing in Temple of Veeshan.  We award armor drops to mains first...but if no mains need it can be awarded to your alts.  In some cases we may sell overflow armor to support guild activities.<br>
<br>
In order to receive awards of Thurgadin Armors you must be Kindly to Coldain.<br>
<br>
In order to receive awards of Skyshrine Armors you must be ALLY to Claws of Veeshan.<br>
<br>
We award our loot based on a loot council.  We weight this by where the specific piece will do the most good for the guild, raid participation, your equipment and your wants.  It is a judgement call on our part solely.  We do pretty well with it but occasionally someone disagrees or knows something we don't.  In those cases take it up privately with Myself or Extrafth.  We will NOT under any circumstance take back an award once it is announced...but if your reasoning is good you may be moved higher on the list for that item the next time it drops.<br>
<br>
Please remember the priority for loot first is to the core tank/pulling group.  Our total guild success depends on these folks.  They, initially will receive what may seem to be more than they're fair share....we don't quit once they're equiped...it will all come to everyone in time.<br>
<br>
For example:  if a high taunt 1hs or 1hb drops EXPECT Raivene to get it...and if she already has it or better EXPECT Lashad to get it.  If they both have it or better then normal rules apply.<br>
<br>
Currently the core pulling and tanking group consists of:<br>
<br>
Raivene - Level 60 Warrior<br>
Lashad - Level 58 Warrior <br>
Extrafth - Level 60 Monk<br>
Sinthala - level 56 Monk<br>
Trevelain - level 56 SK<br>
Vexed - Level 56 SK<br>
<br>
Now before anyone takes the opinion this is a scam to enrich a few accounts, I encourage you to ask members.  Extrafth and I could both be sitting pretty with about a half mil in plat each from MQing thurg armors and such....but we gave it to our members and our affiliates.  Our goal is quite simply to move up and do and see things that we haven't had the chance to before...and equipment is the ticket to that.<br>
<br>
Things on the horizon:<br>
<br>
Epics - You tell us what you need.  As we get the folks available we will schedule raids to obtain epic pieces<br>
<br>
Fear - TBS<br>
<br>
Hate - TBS<br>
<br>
HoT in Tov - November 2nd, 2002<br>
<br>
Ssra temple - Weekly<br>
<br>
That's AD in a nutshell.  Good folks, good times and pretty good loots too....<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
